President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate Judge David Hamilton to the United States 7th Circuit Court of Appeals. Hamilton has served as a federal district judge in Indiana for 14 years. He was appointed as a United States District Judge for the Southern District of Indiana in 1994 and became Chief Judge in January 2008. President Obama praised Hamilton's record of service and fair decisions, stating that he will be a valuable addition to the 7th Circuit. Hamilton previously worked as an associate and partner at the Indianapolis firm of Barnes & Thornburg and served as Counsel to then-Governor Evan Bayh of Indiana. He also served as a member of the Indiana State Recount Commission and as chairman of the Indiana State Ethics Committee. U.S. Senator Dick Lugar and U.S. Senator Evan Bayh expressed their support for Hamilton's confirmation, highlighting his distinguished service and commitment to applying the law fairly. Hamilton is a graduate of Yale Law School and studied in Germany on a Fulbright scholarship. He is also an emeritus member of the board of visitors of the Indiana University School of Law.